ave performed well  By the end of 2008  assets had rebounded off the low to  167 000  4 8  After a rocky first quarter in 2009  the group seems to have regained its footing  For the year through April  assets are up about 5 3  while the S P 500 Index is still down for the year by 3 3  and the S P 400 Index is up 4 2  In October 2008  eight members along with the advisors traveled on the sixth annual trip to New York City  The group attended a number of informative meetings hosted by a variety of firms  including Bloomberg  financial data and software provider  Wilkinson O Grady   Co   a private money manager  Goldman Sachs  wealth management group  and TM Capital  investment bank  The NYC alumni again hosted the cadets to dinner  In March 2009  two cadets and Col  Moreschi attended RISE IX  Redefining Investment Strategy Education  at the University of Dayton  Attended by over 2500 domestic and international students and faculty from over 200 colleges and universities  RISE brings leading investment professionals together with the students and faculty in an exciting and interactive learning environment  RISE offers our cadets exposure to Wall Street professional investors and portfolio managers and members of other college and university student investment clubs  Spring 2009 Newsletter AACSB Accreditation  Major Field Test in Business  Colonel Husted Retires  New Hire   Colonel Scarpaci  Faculty Scholarship  Speakers  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  SBD and ODE Activity  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  Stay Connected  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  