cial data and software provider  Wilkinson O Grady   Co   a private money manager  Goldman Sachs  wealth management group  and TM Capital  investment bank  The NYC alumni again hosted the cadets to dinner  In March 2009  two cadets and Col  Moreschi attended RISE IX  Redefining Investment Strategy Education  at the University of Dayton  Attended by over 2500 domestic and international students and faculty from over 200 colleges and universities  RISE brings leading investment professionals together with the students and faculty in an exciting and interactive learning environment  RISE offers our cadets exposure to Wall Street professional investors and portfolio managers and members of other college and university student investment clubs  Spring 2009 Newsletter AACSB Accreditation  Major Field Test in Business  Colonel Husted Retires  New Hire   Colonel Scarpaci  Faculty Scholarship  Speakers  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  SBD and ODE Activity  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  Stay Connected Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   Cadet Investment Group Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   Cadet Investment Group Home Academics Areas of Study Social Science Economics   Business      Cadet Investment Group The Cadet Investment Group  CIG  was founded in 1986 by the VMI Foundation  The group s mission is to learn about investing  To do this  members serve as investment analysts and portfolio managers  Divided into two teams  each team has its own investment style and methodology  Team A focuses on middle sized growth stocks while team B invests only in large capitalization value stocks  CIG is open to all 3rd  2nd and 1st class cadets  without regard to major  Faculty advisors to the CIG are Col  Cliff West and Col  Bob Moreschi  As of December 31  2007  prior to the 2008 market meltdown  the combined assets were just over  243 000  In October the group hit its low poin